The paper focuses on the safety and resilience of fully autonomous vehicles, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also utilizes machine learning techniques (cs.AI) to develop a fault injection engine. The application of this engine is in the field of robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY), which are relevant to autonomous vehicles. Finally, the paper uses Bayesian methods (cs.LG) to optimize the fault injection process.
